<H3> <TI>   Ranariddh, Hun Sen Return From PRC 21 Jan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2201090794 Phnom Penh AKP in French 0412 GMT 22 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK2201090794 </F>
<F P=104>  Phnom Penh AKP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Phnom Penh 22 Jan (AKP) -- The delegation of the 
Royal Government of Cambodia led by Prince Krompreah Norodom 
Ranariddh and Hun Sen, first and second prime ministers, 
returned to Phnom Penh on Friday [21 January] after an official 
five-day visit to China at the invitation of the Chinese premier. 
  The delegation met with a PRC Government delegation led by 
Premier Li Peng during the visit. The meeting was followed by 
the signing of an agreement by the Cambodian deputy prime 
minister, Prince Norodom Sirivut, and the Chinese State Council 
vice chairman. The agreement concerns a 50-million-yuan 
interest-free loan from the Chinese Government to the Kingdom of 
Cambodia. The delegation visited the center of industrial 
development in Hainan and a textile factory in Guangdong. 
Cambodia's royal delegation also visited His Majesty Norodom 
Sihanouk, king of Cambodia, who is taking medical treatment in 
the Chinese capital. 
  The delegation was received on its return at Pochentong 
airport by Sar Kheng, deputy prime minister and minister of 
interior and public security; Chem Snguon, state minister and 
justice minister; Sam Rangsi, state minister and minister of 
finance and economy; and other high-ranking officials. 
  The representative of the diplomatic corps of the PRC to 
Cambodia was also present. 

