<H3> <TI>   LDP Submits No-Confidence Vote on Ministers </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2201023594 Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database in Japanese 22 
Jan 94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW2201023594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From MAINICHI SHIMBUN in Japanese 22 January Morning </F>
Edition] 
  [Text] On 21 January the Liberal Democratic Party [LDP] 
submitted to House of Representatives Speaker Takako Doi two 
no-confidence motions against Tsutomu Hata, deputy prime 
minister and concurrently foreign minister, and Eijiro Hata, 
agriculture minister, in connection with their handling of the 
opening of the rice market under the new multilateral trade 
negotiations (Uruguay Round). The lower house Committee on 
Rules and Administration will discuss how to deal with the 
LDP-submitted motions at a board of directors meeting on 24 
January. 
  As reasons for the no-confidence motions against them, the 
LDP cited the following: Foreign Minister Hata "neglected to 
take part in the negotiations on his own initiative and to brief 
the Diet on progress in the negotiations; as a result he ruined 
the Diet resolutions." Agriculture Minister Hata "lied to the 
people in replying to Diet interpellations." 

</TEXT>

