  [Text] Tokyo, Jan. 18 KYODO -- Japan will loan Malawi up 
to 7.4 billion yen to support the African nation's programs to 
train entrepreneurs and tackle droughts, the Foreign Ministry 
said Tuesday [18 January]. 
