  [Text] Kathmandu Jan. 20 KYODO -- Japan agreed Thursday 
[20 January] to grant Nepal 1,390,000 dollars to prepare a 
detailed design for air safety equipment at Kathmandu airport 
and a bridge linking the capital with the sister city of Patan, 
the Japanese Embassy said. 
