military dictators of the `Sixth Republic' to suppress and 
stifle it, is little different from the preceding military 
fascist regimes, and, accordingly, it is clear to everyone that 
the fascist `regime' cannot be called a `civilian government'. 
  "Worse still, the South Korean authorities refused to accept 
our offer for mourning visit, a purely humanitarian and 
compatriotic issue, by linking it with the fictitious `nuclear 
problem'. This goes to prove that the `nuclear issue' 
loud-mouthed by them is a product of a sinister political 
purpose. 
  "The Kim Yong-sam group must act with discretion, well aware 
that angry voices condemning this anti-human and rude act are 
ringing out not only among the people of all strata, the 
