<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   KCNA on Foreign Minister Meeting Iran's Mottaki </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2501043994 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0410 GMT 25 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2501043994 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, January 25 (KCNA) -- Vice Premier and 
Foreign Minister Kim Yong-nam Monday met and had a friendly talk 
with the visiting Iranian deputy minister of foreign affairs, 
Manuchehr Mottaki. 
  On the same day, Yang Hyong-sop, chairman of the Supreme 
People's Assembly, met and had a friendly conversation with the 
Iranian Foreign Ministry delegation led by the deputy minister 
at the Mansudae Assembly Hall. 
  On the occasion the head of the delegation expressed the 
hope 
that the Korean people under the wise guidance of the great 
leader President Kim Il-song and the dear leader Comrade Kim 
Chong-il would achieve the reunification of the country at an 
early date. 
  He wished the Korean people greater success in socialist 
construction in the three-year period of adjustment. 

</TEXT>

