<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Accord Signed on Diplomatic Visas </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2501045694 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0428 GMT 25 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2501045694 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, January 25 (KCNA) -- An agreement on the 
abolition of the visa system of diplomatic passport carriers was 
signed here Monday between the governments of the Democratic 
People's Republic of Korea and the Islamic Republic of Iran. 
  Present at the signing ceremony on the Korean side were Vice 
Minister of Foreign Affairs Cho Kyu-il and officials concerned, 
and on the opposite side were the members of the Iranian Foreign 
Ministry delegation led by its Deputy Minister Manuchehr Mottaki 
and the charge d'affaires ad interim of the Iranian Embassy here. 

</TEXT>

