<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hwang Chang-yop, WPK Delegation Visits PRC </TI></H3>
<H4>   Radio Reports Activities </H4>
<F P=102> SK2401095794 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 1300 GMT 23 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK2401095794 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 1300 GMT 23 Jan 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hwang Chang-yop, secretary of the Workers' Party of 
Korea Central Committee, and his entourage visited the Beijing 
Plaza and a newly built housing complex at the Fengtai District 
on 15 January. 
  Hwang Chang-yop and his entourage also visited the Guangzhou 
Labor Movement Training School's Memorial Hall in Guangzhou 
City, Guangdong Province, which was set up by President Mao 
Zedong; the (Tueshu) Park; the Agricultural Science Institute 
and various plants and enterprises in Sunde City and (Puer) 
City, from 17 to 20 January. 
  The group arrived in Shenyang City on 21 January. It visited 
various organizations and plants, including the Liaoning 
Exhibition Hall in Shenyang City on 22 January. During its 
stay, the group was invited to banquets hosted by Comrade Ding 
Guangen, member of the Political Bureau of the CPC Central 
Committee and member of the Secretariat of the CPC Central 
Committee, and the Guangdong Province Committee and Liaoning 
Province Committee of the CPC. Participants of the banquet 
toasted to the long life of the great leader Comrade Kim 
Il-song, the dear leader Comrade Kim Chong-il, and the Chinese 
leaders, including the respected Comrade Jiang Zemin. 

</TEXT>

