<H3> <TI>   Koreans in Japan Thankful for Educational Aid </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2601102194 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1002 GMT 26 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2601102194 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, January 26 (KCNA) -- Korean educational 
workers and scientists in Japan met in Tokyo on Jan. 22 to 
express their thanks to the great leader Generalissimo Kim 
Il-song and the dear leader Marshal Kim Chong-il for the 125th 
installment of educational aid fund and stipends. 
  In his report at the meeting, chairman of the Union of 
Korean 
Teachers in Japan Pak Kwang-taek extended highest honour and 
warmest thanks to the fatherly leader Generalissimo Kim Il-song 
and the dear leader Marshal Kim Chong-il for showing paternal 
loving care for the development of the democratic national 
education of Koreans in Japan. 
  The reporter called on the educational workers to radically 
improve national education of the General Association of Korean 
Residents in Japan (Chongnyon) with the 50th anniversary of the 
August 15 liberation of Korea, the 40th anniversary of the 
formation of Chongnyon and the 17th Congress of Chongnyon one 
year off. 
  Many representatives expressed their resolve. 
  A letter to Generalissimo Kim Il-song was adopted at the 
meeting. 

</TEXT>

