<H3> <TI>   President Kim Il-song Greets Indian Counterpart </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2501113194 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1106 GMT 25 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2501113194 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, January 25 (KCNA) -- President Kim 
Il-song of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea today sent 
a message of greetings to Indian President Shankar Dayal Sharma 
on the occasion of the day of the Republic of India. 
  Noting that since the founding of the Republic the Indian 
people have made great progress in their efforts to promote 
national unity and achieve independent development of the 
country, President Kim Il-song wished the president and people 
of India success in the work to build a new independent and 
prosperous India. 
  He stressed that the traditional relations of friendship and 
cooperation between Korea and India would continue to develop in 
strength in future in accordance with the ideals of 
independence, friendship and non-alignment. 

</TEXT>

