<H3> <TI>   Newspapers Observe India's Independence Day </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2601121094 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1103 GMT 26 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2601121094 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, January 26 (KCNA) -- Papers here today 
observe the day of the Republic of India. 
  The Indian people have made great strides in their efforts 
to 
consolidate national independence and build a prosperous new 
society since the foundation of the republic, MINJU CHOSON in a 
by-lined article says, and continues: 
  The Republic of India, one of the founders of the 
Non-Aligned 
Movement, is pursuing the non-aligned foreign policy. India is 
developing the friendly and cooperative relations with different 
countries including neighbouring countries and striving for 
peace in Asia and the rest of the world. 
  The Governments and peoples of Korea and India, non-aligned 
countries in Asia, established the bonds of friendship and 
cooperation long ago and have developed it. 
  The Korean people, believing that the ties between the two 
peoples will further strengthen in future, sincerely hope that 
the Indian people will make greater progress in the endeavours 
for the independent development and prosperity of the country. 

</TEXT>

