<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Visitors' Praise of Kim Chong-il Cited </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2501104094 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1021 GMT 25 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2501104094 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["`Comrade Kim Chong-il Is an Illustrious Leader With </F>
Literary and Military Accomplishments and Loyalty and Filial 
Piety'" -- KCNA headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, January 25 (KCNA) -- Foreign visitors to 
Korea speak highly of the feats and personality of the dear 
leader Comrade Kim Chong-il. 
  Mady Ndao who had visited Korea in the capacity of special 
envoy of the Senegalese president said he keenly felt that His 
Excellency Kim Chong-il is the greatest thinker and theoretician 
of the present era and ever-victorious iron-willed brilliant 
commander with literary and military accomplishments. 
  "His Excellency Kim Chong-il has steadily developed and 
enriched the immortal chuche idea and strengthened and developed 
the Korean People's Army into steel-like Armed Forces that can 
defeat any aggressors at one blow," he noted. 
  Alhaji Adam Bukhari Ziblim, general secretary of the 
National 
Convention Party of Ghana, had this to say: 
  "The dear leader Comrade Kim Chong-il is a great man 
possessed of courage, tested organising ability and iron will. 
I am struck with admiration at his precious feats and 
energetic guidance in strengthening the Korean People's Army 
into matchless ranks and building many monumental edifices. 
  "The looks of the Korean people who are marching forward in 
soaring spirits, full of confidence in victory, convinced me 
that no one on earth is a match for this people." 
  Toyohide Araki who led a delegation of the Japan Society for 
the Study of Kimilsongism is quoted as saying: 
  "Dear Comrade Kim Chong-il is a great man of the great men 
with both literary and military accomplishments. 
  "The world is unstinting in praising him for humbling the 
U.S. imperialists." 
  P. Mabiti, an MP of Tanzania, said he was struck with wonder 
at the phenomenal development of Korea. 
  "The proud achievements gained by Korea are all a shining 
fruition of the independent politics of the great leader Comrade 
Kim Il-song and the tested, veteran leadership of the dear 
leader Comrade Kim Chong-il with literary and military 
accomplishments and loyalty and filial piety, who is leading the 
revolutionary cause to victory with his matchless grit and 
rock-firm faith," he stressed. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

