<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Papers Carry Kim Il-song 1994 Address </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2401053994 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0501 GMT 24 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2401053994 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, January 24 (KCNA) -- The New Year address 
of the great leader President Kim Il-song was carried by the 
Indian papers SAVERA and PROLETARIAN ERA, Yemeni papers AL-RAYY 
AL-'AM and AL-MUSTAQBAL, the Tunisian paper ANNONCES, the 
Egyptian paper MIDDLE EAST OBSERVER, the Senegalese paper LE 
TEMOIN, the Nepalese paper JAN SANGARUSHA, the Finnish paper 
TYOKANSAN SANOMAT, the Ghanaian paper GHANAIAN TIMES, the Syrian 
paper NIDAL SHAAM, the Burkinabe paper SIDWAYA and the 
Palestinian magazine PALESTINE AL-SHURA. 
  Seminars on the New Year address were also held by the 
society for the study of the chuche idea of Guinean youth and 
students and at the Harare, Zimbabwe, Centre for the Study of 
the Chuche Philosophy. 
  The reporters and speakers said that the New Year address, a 
highly important work indicating the way for the DPRK to achieve 
greater victory and success, is of universal significance to all 
the progressive countries. 
  The idea of establishing new international political and 
economic orders and developing South-South cooperation set forth 
in the New Year address is a fighting programme to which 
developing countries should hold fast. 
  A lecture on the New Year address was given by the Lugazi 
branch of the Uganda-DPRK Friendship Association and reading 
sessions on it were held by the Maputo city committee of the 
Momzambique Liberation Front Party and the West African 
Examinations Council branch of the Ghanaian National Institute 
of the Chuche Idea. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

