<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   WPK Sends Greetings to French Party Congress </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2401112194 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1104 GMT 24 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2401112194 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, January 24 (KCNA) -- The Central 
Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea [WPK] Monday sent a 
message of greetings to the 28th Congress of the French 
Communist Party. 
  The message says over the past 70 years the French Communist 
Party has been engaged in a vigorous struggle against war and 
fascism and for defence of political right of broad segments of 
the French working masses and their freedom, democracy, the 
sovereignty of the nation, and the socialist cause and expresses 
full support and firm solidarity for the struggle of the French 
Communist Party for peace and socialism. 
  The message expresses the belief that the friendly and 
cooperative relations between the two parties will grow stronger 
and develop in the future and wishes the French Communist Party 
new success in the congress. 

</TEXT>

