<H3> <TI>   WPK Greets Britannic Communist Party Chief </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2401060194 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0505 GMT 24 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2401060194 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, January 24 (KCNA) -- The Central 
Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea sent a message of 
greetings on January 20 to Michael Hicks upon his reelection as 
general secretary of the Britannic Communist Party. 
  Believing that the friendly and cooperative relations 
between 
the two parties will further develop in the future in the common 
idea for socialism, the message wished him success in his 
responsible work for defending the interests of the working 
masses including the working class and expanding and 
strengthening the party ranks. 

</TEXT>

