<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kim Chong-il Sends Thanks for Army-People Unity </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2401053794 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0457 GMT 24 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2401053794 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, January 24 (KCNA) -- The dear leader 
Comrade Kim Chong-il sent thanks to the war veterans in Nangnang 
district of Pyongyang, teachers and students of the Pyongyang 
financial cadres school, employees of the Haeju City Commercial 
Administration Office in South Hwanghae Province, Chong Son-yo, 
secretary of the Primary Party Committee of the Potonggang 
district people's hospital of Pyongyang, and Yim Sin-ok, worker 
of Hamhung Restaurant, who set examples in assisting the 
People's Army. 
  The speakers at the meetings held to convey the thanks said 
that it is the sacred duty of citizens to love and assist the 
People's Army soldiers. But, we have the honor and happiness of 
receiving the thanks from the supreme commander, they stressed. 
  They evinced their determination to give more assistance to 
the People's Army and bring the traditional traits of 
army-people unity into fuller play. 

</TEXT>

