<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Socialism Claimed as `Superior' to Capitalism </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2601120694 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1119 GMT 26 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2601120694 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Way Out Is To Rebuild Socialism" -- KCNA headline] </F>
  [Text] Pyongyang, January 26 (KCNA) -- However desperately 
the imperialists and reactionaries may try, they can neither 
dampen the aspiration of people for socialism nor turn back the 
trend of times, declares NODONG SINMUN in a by-lined article 
today. 
  The article says: 
  All manner of contradictions peculiar to the capitalist 
system give rise to chaos and crisis in politics, the economy, 
ideology and morality in those countries where capitalism has 
been revived. 
  Such catastrophic situation in those countries is entirely 
attributable to the reactionary nature of socio-economic reforms 
that have brought the revival of capitalism. 
  Hence, the quicker the process of reform, the more serious 
crisis and chaos. 
  The only way out of the crisis in the countries where 
capitalism has been revived is to rebuild socialism. 
  Socialism is incomparably superior to capitalism. 
  Capitalism is an anti-popular society where exploitation of 
man by man prevails and a tiny handful of exploiting class lord 
it over, a corrupt society based on extreme egoism. 
  But, socialism is a genuine society for the people where the 
popular masses are masters of everything and everything serves 
them, a superior society based on collectivism. 
  If the basic principles of socialist construction had been 
maintained and the advantages of the socialist system brought 
into full play, frustration of socialism and revival of 
capitalism would not have taken place at all in some countries. 
  Grudge against the revival of capitalism is swelling up and 
aspiration for socialism growing strong among the people in 
those countries who have realised it through bitter experiences. 
  The imperialists and reactionaries are making every 
conceivable effort to check the revival of socialism. 
  This is a move to block the social progress of those 
countries and put the peoples of those countries under the 
permanent yoke of domination and subordination. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-48462 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreas017_c_94033" </HT>


