<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   KCNA Highlights Achievements in Fishing </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2401110294 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1034 GMT 24 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2401110294 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, January 24 (KCNA) -- Korean fishermen are 
reporting remarkable achievements in fishing. 
  According to data available at the State Fisheries 
Commission, the January plan for aquatic products was fulfilled 
at 115 percent, of which fishes at 178 percent, on the 23rd of 
January. 
  In this period, the South Hamgyong Provincial General Bureau 
of Fisheries topped its fishing plan for the first half of the 
year and the General Bureau of Pelagic Fishing its first 
quarterly target. 
  The fisheries stations caught 40 to 50 tons of fish, 70 tons 
at maximum, per net by nimbly occupying the central fishing 
ground and applying advanced fishing methods. 

</TEXT>

