<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   KCNA Reports Increased Industrial Production </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2501123794 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1058 GMT 25 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2501123794 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, January 25 (KCNA) -- Working people 
across Korea are increasing production to register proud 
achievements this year, the first year of the period of 
adjustment. 
  The Kaechon coal mine is topping its daily quotas by 40 to 
50 
percent, concentrating efforts on tunneling to create an 
additional production capacity of two million tons by the end of 
April. The coal miners there have created several new cutting 
faces and are boosting production. 
  The pipeline transport station of the Kim Chaek iron and 
steel complex has lifted the daily transport of iron headings 
through the pipeline extending 100 kilometres from Musan and 
Chongjin by 50 percent entering this year over the daily average 
towards the end of last year. 
  The Pukchang thermal power complex increased electricity 
output by 30 percent as of January 24 as against that in the 
same period of the previous month. 
  Industrial establishments under the Ministry of Chemical 
Industry are registering signal achievements in the efforts to 
boost fertilizer production this year in which falls the 30th 
anniversary of the publication of the great rural theses. 
  Many units including the State Fisheries Commission and the 
North Phyongan Provincial Management Office of minor power 
stations beat their January targets ahead of schedule. 

</TEXT>

