<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   KCNA Reports on Development of New Ceramic Art </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2501102294 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1001 GMT 25 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2501102294 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, January 25 (KCNA) -- A new ceramic art 
more simple and effective than the old technique has been 
developed in Korea. 
  So far a mixture of four to six kinds of raw materials was 
baked at high temperature. But the new technique requires the 
baking of one kind of raw material at low temperature. The new 
method increases the kiln efficiency two or three fold. 
  In the past it took 12 to 14 hours to get powder of mixed 
materials, while the new technique requires less than eight 
hours. 
  The new method is favorable for transport because it relies 
on the raw material rich in different parts of the country. It 
also saves fuel, electricity and manpower considerably. 
  The porcelainware made by the new method is light, solid and 
low in absorption rate. When used as a building material, its 
life span is considerably lengthened. 
  The method has been developed by teachers and researchers of 
the geological department of Kim Il-song University and 
technicians of the Taesong ceramic factory. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

