<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   New Botanical Gallery Built in Pyongyang </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2401105394 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1022 GMT 24 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2401105394 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, January 24 (KCNA) -- A new botanical 
specimen gallery has been built in the Central Botanical Garden 
which is situated at the foot of scenic Mt. Taesong in Pyongyang. 
  The total floor space of the gallery is 2,000 square metres. 
  The gallery will permanently preserve hundreds of thousands 
of specimens including those taken from more than 2,800 plants 
presented by foreign heads of state and public figures to the 
great leader President Kim Il-song and the dear leader Comrade 
Kim Chong-il. 
  The gallery consists of a gift plant specimen room, a Korean 
plant specimen room, a world plant specimen room, a trunk piece 
and seed specimen room, a provincial plant specimen room, a 
dendrolite specimen room and an immersion specimen room. 
  It also has an automation gauge room for scientific and 
technical preservation of specimens and specimen lending and 
study rooms and research rooms. 
  At the gallery scientists and researchers will develop new 
varieties by comparatory analysis of plants of foreign countries 
and trace the course of the evolution of plants through fossil 
plants. 
  Rich materials for writing books will be available at the 
gallery. 
  The gallery will exchange plant specimens with many 
countries. 
  The botanical specimen gallery which will make a big 
contribution to the development of the country's botany will be 
opened soon. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

