<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Anti-Dumping Attacks' Up Since GATT Conclusion </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2401030694 Seoul YONHAP in English 0200 GMT 24 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2401030694 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, Jan. 24 (YONHAP) -- South Korea faces a 
shower of foreign anti-dumping attacks as the Uruguay Round 
accord, slated to take effect next year, includes shields 
against anti-dumping abuses, the Korea Trade Promotion Corp. 
(KOTRA) said Monday. 
  Canada landed a preliminary dumping margin of 45.6 percent 
on 
Korean steel plate on Jan. 17 and as a result Tongkuk Steel Mill 
Co. has to make deposits equal to the amount for its exports to 
the North American country. 
  On Jan. 6, the Argentine Government said it would slap 
punitive anti-dumping tariffs on Korean-made men's shirts of 
under 4.95 U.S. dollars on its market at the free-on-board rate. 
  Mexico recently announced that it will continue 
investigation 
of Goldstar Co., Daewoo Electronics Co., Sonil Metal Co., and 
Hanil Precision Industries Co., which are suspected of exporting 
at between 5.15 percent and 55.47 percent less than fair prices. 
  Under preliminary dumping findings of between 6.77 percent 
and 29.16 percent on high-density polyethylene and between 11.24 
percent and 17.39 percent on low-density items, the Taipei 
Government went into final screening of Korean exporters. 
  At complaints by local manufacturers, Australia embarked on 
a 
preliminary investigation into Korean and Singaporean PVC 
(polyvinvyl chloride) homopolymer earlier in the month. 
  Hanyang Chemical Corp., Lucky Corp., Goldenbell Co., and 
Samsung Chemical Industries Co. are under charges of dumping 
between 10 percent and 38 percent. The preliminary ruling is 
due sometime in April. 
  India, Korea's major synthetic resin buyer, is said to be 
preparing an anti-dumping attack on the Korean export. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

