<H3> <TI>   Defense Ministry To Export Jets to Thailand </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2401013894 Seoul TONG-A ILBO in Korean 24 Jan 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> SK2401013894 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul TONG-A ILBO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] It was learned on 23 January that the Defense 
Ministry will export about 10 F5AB fighter planes of the ROK Air 
Force to Thailand at the cost of from $1 to $1.5 million each. 
F5AB is an outmoded fighter plane model that was introduced 
from the United States late in the sixties. This is the first 
time the ROK has exported planes. The United States originally 
opposed the ROK's plan to export planes of this model, but has 
recently consented to it. 

</TEXT>

