<F P=100> Laos </F>
<H3> <TI>   Talks Held With SRV Foreign Relations Delegation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2401142994 Vientiane Vitthayou Hengsat Radio Network in 
Lao 1200 GMT 24 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2401142994 </F>
<F P=104>  Vientiane Vitthayou Hengsat Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Lao </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Talks were held at the Vang Sadet residence in 
Vientiane capital this morning between a Foreign Relations 
Committee delegation of the Lao People's Democratic Republic 
[LPDR] and a SRV Foreign Relations Committee delegation. The 
LPDR delegation was headed by Somsavat Lengsavat, deputy chief 
of the Foreign Relations Committee, while the Vietnamese 
delegation was headed by Do Van Tai, deputy chief of the Foreign 
Relations Committee. The SRV delegation is currently on a 
friendship visit to the LPDR. 
  In the talks, the two sides informed one another of their 
achievements in various fields, particularly in fulfilling the 
agricultural production plan and in carrying out economic work 
and the export and import trade in 1993. They also informed 
each other of the gradual developments of various services, for 
example the development of the marketing mechanism under state 
management. The two sides have agreed to further strengthen the 
special fraternal solidarity and to further enhance and 
consolidate the already normalized relations of friendship 
between the two countries. They have also unanimously agreed to 
improve and broaden cooperation with other friendly countries of 
the world. 
  The Vietnamese delegation arrived in Vientiane at noon on 23 
January for a week's visit to Laos. During its stay, the 
delegation is scheduled to visit some economic and cultural 
establishments in Vientiane Municipality, Vientiane Province, 
and Luang Prabang Province. 

</TEXT>

