<H3> <TI>   ROK Fighter Jet Sale Still `Under Discussion' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2501072194 Bangkok Radio Thailand Network in Thai 0530 GMT 
24 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2501072194 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok Radio Thailand Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Thai </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Regarding a news report that South Korea will sell 
F-5 fighter jets to Thailand, Air Force Assistant Commander Air 
Chief Marshal Samat Sotsathit said that the deal was still under 
discussion. He said that although this type of the fighter jet 
is no longer produced, the Thai Air Force is using it. There is 
no problem regarding spareparts because production of spare 
parts has not been discontinued. 

