<F P=100> Cambodia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ranariddh Discusses `Problems To Be Solved' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2601082194 Phnom Penh National Radio of Cambodia Network 
in Cambodian 0430 GMT 26 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2601082194 </F>
<F P=104>  Phnom Penh National Radio of Cambodia Network 
in Cambodian 0430 GMT 26 Jan 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Cambodian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Speech by First Prime Minister Prince Krompreah Norodom </F>
Ranariddh at the University of Fine Arts in Phnom Penh on 25 
January -- recorded] 
  [Summary From Poor Reception] I assure you that the Royal 
Government will try to solve problems while taking the interests 
of our compatriot traders into account. Whatever I do is in the 
name of the Royal Government. There have been cases when it was 
said that problems could not be solved; yet the Royal Government 
solved them without any demonstrations occurring. But there is 
no need to praise Ranariddh or say that he is a hero. 
  There are still many problems to be solved, such as the 
schools lacking textbooks and teachers, poverty in rural areas, 
insecurity, and so forth. We should not focus exclusively on 
the problems with the Olympic Market. The problem will be 
solved without putting Cambodia's interests at risk. This 
should be done properly. I am very concerned about unauthorized 
checkpoints. This is a problem we must solve. I urge all of 
you to be considerate and sympathetic to the Royal Government. 
Show the international community that Cambodia has no problems; 
that we have social and political stability. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

