<F P=100> Cambodia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ranariddh Meets Austrian Deputy Foreign Minister </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2601085394 Phnom Penh National Radio of Cambodia Network 
in Cambodian 0430 GMT 26 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2601085394 </F>
<F P=104>  Phnom Penh National Radio of Cambodia Network 
in Cambodian 0430 GMT 26 Jan 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Cambodian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] On the morning of 25 January, Prince Krompreah 
Norodom Ranariddh received at his residence the Austrian 
delegation led by His Excellency [H.E.] Wolfgang Schallenberg, 
Austrian deputy foreign minister. 
  The first prime minister talked about the efforts of the 
Royal Government of Cambodia [RGC] to search for peace, national 
reconciliation, and particularly in national rehabilitation and 
reconstruction, under the correct leadership of his majesty the 
king. Prince Krompreah further said that the RGC has four goals 
for the investment sector, namely political stability, higher 
wages, identifying land for leasing, and lower taxes. 
  Concerning the Khmer Rouge issue, Prince Krompreah said that 
this cannot be considered a big issue. Furthermore, the RGC 
will make Sihanoukville a duty-free zone for investment. He 
further said that as for agriculture, the royal government has 
paid great attention to vigorously promoting the standard of 
living by paying attention to clearing networks of canals, 
planting trees and other crops, and ending the clearing of 
forests. 
  Schallenberg expressed profound thanks for Cambodian efforts 
to rehabilitate and rebuild the country. He further said that 
along with providing assistance to rebuild the hydropower 
station at Kirirom, the Austrian Government will continue to 
contribute to assisting the Cambodian Government and people 
within the lofty Austrian-Cambodian ties of friendship. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

