<H3> <TI>   Bosnian President Arrives for Two-Day Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2501132094 Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network in 
Indonesian 1200 GMT 25 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2501132094 </F>
<F P=104>  Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Indonesian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Indonesia has again reiterated its proposal that 
the arms embargo against Bosnia be lifted because of the 
unbalanced arms strength. This was stated by Minister/State 
Secretary Murdiono to newsmen at Merdeka Palace an hour ago, 
after Bosnian President Alija Izetbegovic paid a courtesy visit 
on President Suharto. 
  According to Minister Murdiono, Indonesia is making a 
continuous effort to support the Bosnian people's struggle. 
  Bosnian President Alija Izetbegovic, who flew to Jakarta 
this 
afternoon of his own desire, is making the working visit to 
Indonesia after visiting Malaysia and Brunei Darussalam. 

