<F P=100> Indonesia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Suharto Meets Bosnian President </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2601052794 Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network in 
Indonesian 0500 GMT 26 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2601052794 </F>
<F P=104>  Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Indonesian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] President Suharto says it is impossible for 
Indonesia to send troops to Bosnia-Herzegovina because of the 
different war doctrines [doktrin perang] of the two countries. 
Discussing the outcome of today's talks between President 
Suharto and visiting Bosnian President Alija Izetbegovic in 
Jakarta, Minister-State Secretary Murdiono said that even though 
Indonesia will not send troops to the former Yugoslav republic, 
it supports the Bosnian people's struggle against Serbia and 
Croatia. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

