<F P=100> Indonesia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Vice President Meets Papua New Guinean Minister </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2501072394 Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network in 
Indonesian 0600 GMT 25 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2501072394 </F>
<F P=104>  Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Indonesian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Indonesia is ready to continue defense and security 
cooperation, particularly military training with Papua New 
Guinea [PNG]. Vice President Try Sutrisno expressed Indonesia's 
readiness to do this during a courtesy call by PNG Defense 
Minister Paul Tohian at his residence on Diponegoro Street in 
Jakarta today. The visit is aimed at enhancing bilateral 
relations, particularly in defense and security. 
  According to Defense Minister Paul Tohian, to enable the 
establishment of a national language, a number of ethnic groups 
in the country, which has a population of four million and 700 
languages, need to be given a new formula. The PNG defense 
minister urged Indonesia to receive a PNG delegation for an APEC 
[Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation] meeting to be held in 
Jakarta this year. 
  The PNG guest, whose visit will end on 30 January, will 
visit 
the Army Industry, the Nusantara Aircraft Industry, the National 
Shipyard, the Ammunition Plant, and tourist spots in Jakarta and 
Yogyakarta. He will also observe military rural assistance 
programs undertaken by military personnel in Indonesia. He will 
fly from Surabaya to Irian Jaya, where he will visit border 
villages. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

