<F P=100> Indonesia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister on Official Visit to Yemen </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2401112894 Jakarta ANTARA in English 0930 GMT 24 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK2401112894 </F>
<F P=104>  Jakarta ANTARA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Jakarta, Jan 24 (ANTARA) -- Foreign Affairs Minister 
Ali Alatas is on an official visit to Yemen from January 22 to 
27, 1994 at the invitation of his Yemeni counterpart. 
  His agenda in Yemen include meetings with the Yemeni Foreign 
Affairs Minister, Trade Minister, Minister of Development 
Planning Dr. 'Abd-al-Karim al-Iryani and Industry Minister 
Mohammad Sa'id al- 'Attar, according to the minister's programme 
received from the Yemeni embassy here Monday. 
  Minister Alatas is also scheduled to pay courtesy calls on 
President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, Prime Minister Haydar al-'Attas 
and Vice President 'Ali Salim al-Bid. 
  A bilateral cooperation agreement between Indonesia and 
Yemen 
is also expected to be signed during his stay in Yemen. 
  Alatas' visit is the first visit ever made by an Indonesian 
official to Sana'a since the reunification of north and south 
Yemen in May 1990. 
  Indonesia opened an embassy in Sana'a in 1992 and Yemen has 
had an embassy in Jakarta since 1990. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

